results.name: Number of non-Hamiltonian unlabeled n-vertex digraphs (with loops).
comment: A digraph is Hamiltonian if it contains a directed cycle passing through every vertex exactly once.
link: Gus Wiseman, Non-isomorphic representatives of the a(3) = 80 non-Hamiltonian digraphs.
example: Non-isomorphic representatives of the a(2) = 7 digraph edge-sets:
xref: The case without loops is A326222.
The undirected case is A246446 (without loops) or A326239 (with loops).
Unlabeled digraphs not containing a Hamiltonian path are A326224.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Jun 15 2019
